<DIV>I'm a bit confused on why they've chosen this method of implementation for the new adventures:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1. With the current low population of "Active" players, it's been close to impossible to get ldons, and many days</DIV>
<DIV>pickup groups. Now that there are 2 seperate camps with faction hits reducing people available for groups at</DIV>
<DIV>either camp will be 1/2, or less, unless one manages to stay netural'ish, by doing adventures in both camps on a regular basis.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2. Not knowing what items are available at each camp, before selecting which camp to faction with: how would one </DIV>
<DIV>know what is the best camp, in the long run, to take adventures from for thier class?&nbsp; From what I've read you can currently</DIV>
<DIV>only see items from 300-340??&nbsp;points &amp; below.&nbsp; Hopefully there will be a complete list of items available for each camp</DIV>
<DIV>soon.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3. Unless there are different items for each camp, why even go the faction route?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4. Are there also faction + &amp; - for each camp killing mobs while in the new DoN missions?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
